description:
## Why

Once AppEvent::SessionReady carries supports_ephemeral, AppState needs to store it so the render pass can make conditional decisions. Without this, the field is received and discarded.

## What to do

In crates/jmap-chat-egui/src/app.rs:

1. Add field to AppState:
```rust
pub supports_ephemeral: bool,  // false until SessionReady received
```
Default: false (safe: hides the feature until server confirms support).

2. In the SessionReady match arm:
```rust
AppEvent::SessionReady { api_url, account_id, supports_ephemeral } => {
    self.api_url = api_url;
    self.account_id = account_id;
    self.supports_ephemeral = supports_ephemeral;
}
```

3. In the UI render pass (ui.rs), gate the typing indicator row and presence badges:
```rust
if app.supports_ephemeral {
    // render typing indicator row
    // render presence badge on contact list items
}
```

If the render pass does not currently show typing or presence UI at all (stub), just ensure the field exists and is threaded — the gating can be a comment placeholder until UI work is done.

## Acceptance criteria

- AppState.supports_ephemeral initialises to false
- Set to true only when SessionReady carries supports_ephemeral: true
- UI does not render typing/presence elements when false
- cargo test passes
